article.headline: Idaho 70, UC Riverside 65
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Idaho's Tanoris Shepard made a key 3-pointer and had a crucial steal in the final 1:23 to lift the Vandals to a 70-65 win over UC Riverside Saturday. Shepard's 3-pointer started a 10-3 run to end the game for Idaho (12-13, 8-7), winner of six straight at home and seven of its last eight. Tyrone Hayes scored 14 points and grabbed seven rebounds for Idaho, while Rashaad Powell and Dwayne Williams added 12 points apiece. Kevin Butler led Riverside (8-14, 5-9) with 18 points, while Vili Morton added 13 points and seven rebounds. With Idaho leading 65-62 with 30 seconds to play, Shepard stripped opposing point guard Mark Peters in the open court, was fouled and hit the first of six Idaho free throws down the stretch to clinch the victory.
